                            data-srcset="https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/240805-CHIN-WORKER-03191_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_quality_95_embedColorProfile_true.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=75&amp;q=70&amp;w=75&amp;s=d185f720cfac9d314c559ea2b4be0d36 75w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/240805-CHIN-WORKER-03191_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_quality_95_embedColorProfile_true.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=150&amp;q=70&amp;w=150&amp;s=9f2bd0e6b6019079a5076d55615a155f 150w, https://img.assets-d.propublica.org/v5/images/240805-CHIN-WORKER-03191_maxWidth_3000_maxHeight_3000_ppi_72_quality_95_embedColorProfile_true.jpg?crop=focalpoint&amp;fit=crop&amp;fp-x=0.5&amp;fp-y=0.5&amp;h=400&amp;q=70&amp;w=400&amp;s=de91fab9379699c05935b2bd28aca983 400w"
                            />
                    </div>
                
            
            <div class="story-promo__info" dir="auto">
                <strong class="story-promo__hed">Escaping Oklahoma: A Worker’s Story From Inside an Illegal Marijuana Operation</strong>
                            </div>
        </a>

    
</aside>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="91.0">Meanwhile, U.S. overdose deaths fell by 33% compared with the previous year, according to <a href="https://www.dni.gov/files/ODNI/documents/assessments/ATA-2025-Unclassified-Report.pdf#page=5">the annual threat assessment by the U.S. intelligence community</a> released March 25. The drop may be tied to the increased availability of naloxone, a drug for treating overdoses, the report said.</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="92.0">The threat assessment report warned that “China likely will struggle to sufficiently constrain” companies and criminal groups involved in the U.S. fentanyl trade, “absent greater law enforcement actions.”</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="93.0">Cronin, the former federal prosecutor, went on to become chief investigative counsel for the House Select Committee. He led last year’s inquiry into China’s role in the fentanyl crisis. The committee’s review of seven Chinese company websites <a href="https://docs.house.gov/meetings/ZS/ZS00/20240416/117142/HRPT-118-1.pdf#page=28">found over 31,000 instances</a> of firms offering illegal chemicals during a period of about three months in early 2024.</p>
        
    
                    
<p data-pp-blocktype="copy" data-pp-id="94.0">Undercover communications with the firms “revealed an eagerness to engage in clearly illicit drug sales,” the report says, “with no fear of reprisal.”</p>
        
    
                    <div class="article-body__bottom-notes" data-pp-location="bottom-note">
                                    

                                    
        <div class="article-body__note article-body__note--contributor-line" data-pp-location="bottom-note" >
                        <p><a href="https://www.propublica.org/people/kirsten-berg">Kirsten Berg</a> contributed research.</p>

        </div>

    
            </div><!-- end .article-body__bottom-notes -->
        
    </div>

    <footer class="article-footer" data-pp-location="article footer">
        
    
        
